results.occurrenceRemarks: Elephant Ears (Taro) has been rapidly invading the creek banks throughout Great Hills Park, having been introduced from cultivated plants upstream in one or more yards or detention ponds.  Efforts are being made (locally) to stem the tide of this invasion.

results.occurrenceRemarks: Patches of these Elephant Ears are common along the banks of San Felipe Creek in Moore Park in Del Rio.  Not as abundant as other infestations (e.g. San Marcos River, etc.) but still of concern.
